<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="NTM12.10">
<l>maṉṉu maturai toṭakkamāka vaṇtuva rāpati taṉṉaḷavun</l>
<l>taṉṉait tamaruyttup peyyavēṇṭit tāḻkuḻa lāḷtuṇin tatuṇivai</l>
<l>poṉṉiyal māṭampo lintutōṉṟum putuvaiyar kōṉviṭṭu cittaṉkōtai</l>
<l>yiṉṉicai yālcoṉṉa ceñcoṉmālai yēttaval lārkkiṭam vaikuntamē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Vaikuṇṭha is the place for</l>
<l>those capable of praingly [recite] the garland of excellent words uttered</l>
<l rend="indent">with sweet music,</l>
<l>— by Kōtai, [daughter of] Viṣṇucitta, the lord of Villiputtūr that appears shining</l>
<l rend="indent">with mansions made of gold—</l>
<l>[that spoke of] the determination that the girl with locks [hanging] low had,</l>
<l rend="indent">Wishing her people to send and let go of [her to places]</l>
<l>Beginning from Mathurā [where He lives] permanently to the fertile Dvarakā city.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
